{"TopicId":149146,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Open Shield on Docking Port","CreatedByName":"SPD13","CreatedById":165993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-02T16:15:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SPD13","CreatedById":165993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-02T16:15:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am working on the script module for MechJeb to automate flights using the excellent MechJeb module.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am facing a problem: How can i programmatically open the Shield of a shielded Docking Port?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this a function of the \u0022Part\u0022 or a function of the \u0022ModuleDockingNode\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T11:04:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe cfg has a ModuleAnimateGeneric. That s what controls the shield.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit and notice the \u003Cspan class=\u0022pl-k\u0022\u003EdeployAnimationController\u003C/span\u003E value on ModuleDockingNode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-03T11:04:49Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2016 11:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by sarbian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SPD13","CreatedById":165993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T13:19:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGeat! Thank you \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the ModuleDockingNode, there is a \u0022 \u003Cfont face=\u0022Menlo\u0022\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EdeployAnimator\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E \u0022 and i can call the \u0022Toggle()\u0022 method on it to open/close the shield.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022 \u003Cfont face=\u0022Menlo\u0022\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EdeployPercent\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E \u0022 on the animator will tell if the shield is open (100) or closed (0).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022 \u003Cfont face=\u0022Menlo\u0022\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EactionAvailable\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E \u0022 will tell if this is a shielded dock or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SPD13","CreatedById":165993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T14:55:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: hmm... no, in fact \u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:Menlo;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EdeployPercent\u003C/span\u003E\u0022 is always \u0022100\u0022, even when the shield is closed...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SPD13","CreatedById":165993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T16:48:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha, i found\u00A0a way \u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u0022\u003Cfont face=\u0022Menlo\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EdeployAnimator\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EProgress\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u0022 is \u00220\u0022 when closed and \u00221\u0022 when opened.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}